properties.areaDesc: Bays and Waterways from Baffin Bay to Port Aransas
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 9 at 9:46PM CST until January 11 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Corpus Christi TX
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, south winds 20 to 25 knots with
gusts up to 35 knots and rough waters expected.

* WHERE...Bays and Waterways from Baffin Bay to Port Aransas.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 6 PM CST this
evening. For the Gale Warning, from 9 AM Friday to midnight
CST Friday night.

* IMPACTS...Gale force winds and high seas will result in
dangerous marine conditions which could result in capsized or
damaged vessels.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong offshore flow will develop beyond
this, once a cold front moves through Friday night.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM FRIDAY TO MIDNIGHT CST FRIDAY NIGHT
